<title>UK: Associations to announce mkt conventions for euro.</title>
<headline>Associations to announce mkt conventions for euro.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Five of the leading international financial trade associations will announce recommended market conventions to be used for financial transactions in euro, following European Economic and Monetary Union (EMU), a statement said on Friday.</p>
<p>The conventions, supported by Euroclear and CEDEL, will be announced next Thursday in London.</p>
<p>&quot;The associations believe that harmonised conventions will encourage transparency and therefore liquidity for the new euro markets, and, secondly will avoid confusion and disputes between market participants,&quot; the statement said.</p>
<p>&quot;This will then allow the financial markets to start systems changes to prepare for EMU. The associations will therefore be announcing recommended market standards for conventions such as day counts, rate fixing periods and business holidays.&quot;</p>
<p>-- London Newsroom +44 171 542 7718</p>
